item.title: Amanda Knox re-convicted of slander in Italian court
item.description: The court was expected to decide wether Knox had slandered Patrick Lumumba, a Congolese bar owner, in a written statement following Meredith Kercher's 2007 murder.

item.title: June 4, 2024 - Modi declares victory in India election as BJP party faces shock setbacks
item.description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi will serve a third term in office after India's election authority confirmed the National Democratic Alliance coalition headed by his ruling Bharatiya Janata Party won the required 272 seats for a majority.

item.title: Amanda Knox returns to Italian courtroom, looking to clear name in slander case
item.description: An Italian court has re-convicted Amanda Knox of slander, even after she was exonerated in the brutal 2007 murder of her British roommate while the two were exchange students in Italy

item.description: Despite a long history of problems and delays, NASA says the Starliner is critical to long-term space station operation.

item.title: Hunter Biden gun trial opening statements
item.description: FBI special agent Erika Jensen, the first witness in Hunter Biden's trial on felony gun charges in Delaware, introduced key evidence Tuesday including text messages and photos taken from Biden's infamous laptop and other devices.
